    <h1 class="text-xl font-semibold">Welcome to MSAO</h1> 
    <p>The Miskatonic Southern Antarctic Observatory (MSAO) is an astronmic observatory at the south pole region, detecting microwave, millimeter-wave, submillimeter-wave region of electromagnetic spectrum. The laboratory is operated by <a class="text-blue-600  underline" href="https://miskatonic-university.org/" target="_blank">Miskatonic University</a>, funded by private donor and is used to detect cosmic microwave background noise in the void region of space.</p>
    <p>Due to the inacccesibility of the location, the MSAO current staff 8, of whom 6 are Ph.D. physicists. The observatory is located near Amundsen–Scott South Pole Station where 49 people are station in the summer and 150 in the winter, where memheber of the station service and supplies the observatory. These researcher and staff comes from univesity across the globe and are station there 6 months at a time.</p>
